# --- m-standard sources policy (per spec §4.4 + sources/README.md) --------
# Always tracked under sources/:
#   - manifest.tsv         (URL -> local path -> sha256 -> fetch_at)
#   - fetch.sh             (recreates the local replica from upstream)
#   - README.md / NOTICE   (license + acquisition notes)
#
# Bulk content is tracked or ignored per the source's redistribution status.

# AnnoStd: crawled offline mirror.
# Redistribution status: NOT verified — content is © MUMPS Development
# Committee + Ed de Moel, with no explicit redistribution licence on the
# site. Repopulate locally with `bash sources/anno/fetch.sh`.
sources/anno/site/

# YottaDB documentation: full clone at the pinned commit. The repo is
# GFDL-1.3, redistribution is permitted, so the working tree is committed
# directly. The inner .git/ is stripped before commit (see clone-ydb.sh)
# rather than tracked: vendoring the bulk content as plain files makes
# the outer repo a self-contained "offline replica" — a fresh clone of
# m-standard already has every YDB doc file on disk, no submodule fetch
# needed. The pinned commit SHA is preserved per-row in
# sources/ydb/manifest.tsv so reproducibility is unaffected.
sources/ydb/repo/.git/
